# ProgramBench Generator

ProgramBench Generator is a faithful, public-paper-based reconstruction of the ProgramBench task-generation pipeline. It builds a gold executable, discovers public executable behavior, generates behavioral tests, evaluates tests against the gold program, filters weak/flaky/dummy-passing tests, scores redundancy and benchmark quality, applies efficiency only after correctness, and packages cleanroom solver/evaluator artifacts.

This is not a toy CSV benchmark. The included demo is intentionally small so the full local pipeline can run quickly, but the code is organized as an extensible ProgramBench-style framework with explicit interfaces for build backends, test-generation backends, coverage adapters, quality gates, cleanroom packaging, and event-sourced provenance.

## Pipeline

```text
repository or local source
-> gold/reference executable
-> behavior surface from docs/help output
-> behavioral pytest suite
-> gold execution and determinism checks
-> assertion-quality linting
-> dummy-binary rejection
-> redundancy and marginal-value scoring
-> correctness-gated efficiency scoring
-> cleanroom solver/evaluator packages
```

## Focused Extensions

- Redundancy-aware test selection and QC routing.
- Correctness-gated efficiency scoring, with speed treated only as a post-correctness signal.
- Event-based benchmark-creation logging.
- Assertion-strength-aware reward shaping using lint results, dummy rejection, and determinism.

Economic-importance labels and scoring are intentionally not included in this MVP.

## Quickstart

```bash
cd programbench-generator
python3 -m pbgen.cli init-task --local-path examples/demo_task/source --task-id mini_cli
python3 -m pbgen.cli build-gold --task-id mini_cli
python3 -m pbgen.cli discover-surface --task-id mini_cli
python3 -m pbgen.cli generate-tests --task-id mini_cli --iterations 2
python3 -m pbgen.cli evaluate-suite --task-id mini_cli
python3 -m pbgen.cli package-cleanroom --task-id mini_cli
python3 -m pbgen.cli export-qc --task-id mini_cli
```

Key outputs are written under `artifacts/mini_cli/`, including `reports/`, `logs/generation_events.jsonl`, generated hidden tests, QC exports, and separated cleanroom packages:

```text
artifacts/mini_cli/packages/
  solver/      # executable, docs, assets, TASK.md
  evaluator/   # hidden tests, reports, logs, gold executable, task.yaml
```

## Current Limitations

The MVP uses a deterministic local heuristic test-generation backend instead of an LLM call. Python/script local builds are fully exercised by the demo; Docker, Rust, Go, C/C++, and Java build/coverage integrations are represented by explicit interfaces and placeholders for future adapters. Coverage-guided iteration is structurally present, while the first runnable demo emphasizes behavioral quality gates over language-specific coverage instrumentation.
